The paper focuses on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) through attention transfer, which is a technique that has been widely used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of attention in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which falls under the cs.CL sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes novel methods for transferring attention, which could be relevant to the cs.AI sub-category. Finally, the paper uses various datasets and CNN architectures, which could be relevant to the cs.NE sub-category.
